  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "In contrast to the current multi-agent benchmark, Tool-RoCo first introduces the Agent-as-Tool concept, which enables LLM agents to treat other agents as manipulable tools and add a novel type of tool, called cooperative tools, to the candidate tool set.",
    "Therefore, the candidate tool set of each agent in Tool-RoCo comprises two categories of tools: common tools and cooperative tools.",
    "Common tools are original high-level actions of the agent directly interacting with the environment, such as PICK, OPEN, and PLACE.",
    "However, collaborative tools are designed to facilitate interaction and coordination with other agents.",
    "Notably, both types of tools are treated at the same hierarchical level of the candidate tool set."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}